snippet.textDisplay: So I wanted to try the wireless stuff but gave up because they're usually crap. I instead bought a base that you thread the charging cords through and you stand all three on every night, they plug right into their cords and are charged in the morning for sure. No "why did the wireless charging stop in the middle of the night?" BS to deal with. Also used the quick charger for my phone so iOS handles charging over time to prolong the battery, etc. It's worked great for the last year, it was like $12 and uses the cords that come with your devices. https://amzn.to/37ttj4L

snippet.textDisplay: I remember when I first heard about wireless charging. I was like, “Oh cool! Well, still convenient that you can just set it on the pad without thinking... right? RIGHT?!! Nope. You have to make sure its centered on the coils. You know what — I’m just going to save 200 bucks and plug it in instead of mindlessly worshipping unnecessary technology.

snippet.textDisplay: 0:23 - There are no channels with a silver-play–button and no videos, it doesn't work like that. Buttons are not automatically sent out when a channel hits 100K subscribers, rather, a YouTube employee is tasked with reviewing the channel to make to make sure it's legit before authorizing a button to be sent. There's a lot of reasons that they can refuse to have a button sent to a channel with 100K+ subscribers, and having no videos (on a video site) is one of them. So no, Justin Y. didn't get a button, instead, he got suspended for spamming, hence the long stretches of disappearances. 😒

snippet.textDisplay: I actually have the Ampere app in my phone,and i love it,its so freaking useful when you have trouble charging a phone and you need to figure out what the problem is or when you buy or replace the charger or its cable,let's face it everyone wears out the charging cables insanely fast,they're not the most resistent things anyway,but did U know that a simply cable can influence the time it takes to charge a phone and can actually make a HUGE difference when charging? i had to deal with it myself and i didn't knew why it took me half a freaking day to charge the phone cuz i didn't knew a cable can make such a huge difference,and the app made me realise how much electricity a good(not my own charger) and perfectly working charger can stuff into my phone and how little my own did,and i gave it some tought and i realised the charger is the same as it was before when it worked perfectly,but i replaced the cable cuz it wore off,and so i discovered the problem,so yeah that app is handy to have around in your phone at any given time
